Bring a large #saucepan{} of @water{for boiling} with a pinch of @salt{pinch} to the 
boil on high heat. Chop the @smoked tofu{1%block} into 2cm cubes and lay them on some
#kitchen roll{} to soak up some of the moisture.

Halve and remove the core from the @red pepper{1}, thinly slice. Halve, peel and 
thinly slice the @eschalion shallot{1}. Roughly chop the @coriander{1%bunch}(roughly chopped,
stalks and all). Zest the @lime{1} then cut in half. Halve the @red chilli{1/2}(deseeded),
deseed and finely chop.

In a small #bowl{}, mix the @hoisin sauce{4%tbsp}, @soy sauce{1.5%tbsp}, lime zest, 
@water{50%ml}, and lime juice.

When the water is boiling add the @egg noodle nests{2} and cook for ~{4%minutes} 
until tender but still a little firm. When cooked, drain in a #colander{}, return 
to the pan and keep to one side.

> TIP: When the noodles are cooked and drained add a drizzle of oil to coat them
and to prevent them from sticking together.

Meanwhile, heat a splash of @oil{splash} in a large #frying pan{} or #wok{} over 
high heat. Add the tofu along with a pinch of salt and @black pepper{pinch}. Stir-fry
until golden, ~{5-6%minutes}. Add the shallot and pepper and stir-fry until starting
to soften, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add the @sugar snap peas{1} to the pan and cook, stirring, for another ~{2%minutes}.
Add the drained noodles, followed by the sauce you made in step 2 and toss together
to coat all the ingredients in the sauce. Bring to a bubble and cook until everything
is piping hot and the sauce has reduced slightly, ~{2-3%minutes}. Season to taste with
a pinch of salt and pepper. Serve in bowls and ENJOY!